<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<Defs>

  <ThingDef ParentName="BuildingBase">
    <defName>GF40K_ImperiumWeaponry</defName>
    <label>weaponry cogitator node</label>
    <description>Cogitator, or a Logic Engine is a sophisticated piece of technology, commonly used by the Adeptus Mechanicus for storing, processing and collecting large amounts of information. Cogitators vary from being purely mechanical in their design to using a combination of organic matter (i.e. - human brains) and liquids for processing power. Most of the cogitators use data-spools for interfacing, so their data processing capacity is rather limited. This particular device is equipped with a light-based neural pathway, which allows it to perform complex operations required to decrypt a selection of ancient STC fragments. They are held in a secure container within the device and should not be tampered with. This cogitator contains the materials necessary for manufacturing weapons, commonly used by the Imperium of Mankind.</description>
